dcterms:description: Daily open, high, low, and close values for all current constituents of the Dow Jones Industrial Average index, obtained from Yahoo Finance.
dcterms:title: Dow Jones Industrial Average constituents (daily open, high, low, close values)

dcterms:description: A common method for estimating volatility based on the standard deviation of returns calculated from daily closing prices.
dcterms:title: Close-to-close volatility estimator

dcterms:creator: M. B. Garman
M. J. Klass
dcterms:description: A volatility estimator that uses open, high, low, and close values, demonstrating higher efficiency factors than the close-to-close estimator.
dcterms:title: Garman-Klass volatility estimator

dcterms:creator: M. Parkinson
dcterms:description: The extreme value method for estimating the variance of the rate of return using high and low prices.
dcterms:title: Parkinson volatility estimator

dcterms:creator: L. C. G. Rogers
S. E. Satchell
dcterms:description: A formula that allows for drifts in volatility estimation, using high, low, and closing prices.
dcterms:title: Rogers-Satchell volatility estimator

dcterms:creator: D. Yang
Q. Zhang
dcterms:description: A drift-independent volatility estimator that is consistent in dealing with opening jumps, based on high, low, open, and close prices.
dcterms:title: Yang-Zhang volatility estimator
